# Content Structure & Organization

## Website Sections

### 1. Hero Section
**Purpose:** Immediate impact and call-to-action

**Content Structure:**
- **Title (H1):** "ReFi Barcelona" or mission statement
- **Body Text:** Concise explanation of what ReFi Barcelona does
- **CTA Button:** Primary action (e.g., "Learn More" with scroll arrow)
- **Hero Image:** Visual representation of the community

**HTML Structure:**
```html
<div class="hero-section">
  <div class="hero-top">
    <div class="hero-title">
      <h1>Main Title</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-image">
      <img src="/static/hero_home.png" alt="Description"/>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-bottom">
    <p class="hero-text">Description paragraph...</p>
    <a href="#about" class="cta-button">Learn More</a>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Content Guidelines:**
- Keep title concise (1-2 lines preferred, max 4)
- Body text should be 2-3 sentences
- CTA should link to next logical section
- Image should be high-quality and relevant

